  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (synthetic adversarial: human-error gap)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). A perfusionist operator role is referenced in the COU; however, all validation activities assume correctly formatted pump-speed and flow-rate inputs supplied by a trained operator. No use-error modes, misuse scenarios, or operator training gaps are characterized or linked. The use-error credibility factor is recorded as not-assessed without documented justification; the narrative cites 'use-error evaluation per IEC 62366 in companion document' but no such document is linked or referenced by identifier.",
