    "rationale": "Seven of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are not assessed, consistent with MRL 2 scoping. The overall credibility assessment is accepted for submission to support the 510(k) hemolysis tolerance decision. Note: the use-error factor does not meet its required level; the assessment team has accepted this gap on the basis of a referenced IEC 62366 companion usability file, though that file has not been formally linked within this credibility package. This constitutes an open action item for the regulatory submission package.",
